The paper deals with the design and analysis of algorithms, specifically hybrid algorithms for solving problems. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of competitive ratios to measure the efficiency of the algorithms suggests a connection to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of searching with multiple robots mentioned in the abstract suggests a connection to the field of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of randomized algorithms suggests a connection to the field of robotics (cs.RO).
